The paper deals with bibliographic analysis, which involves analyzing research areas, citation networks, and paper content. This falls under the broad category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of topic modeling to analyze the bibliographic data suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of CiteSeerX as a dataset suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
